# Naming Conventions & Import Aliases

These are **mandatory rules**, not suggestions. AI agents and contributors MUST follow this table exactly.

## Constraints

| Type | Example | Style |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Folders & base files | `locale-switcher`, `query-client.ts` | kebab-case |
| Component (widget/layout/page) | `UserList.tsx` | PascalCase |
| UI primitives (`components/ui`) | `button.tsx` | kebab-case |
| Helper / util files | `format-date.ts` | kebab-case |
| Hook files | `use-users.ts` | kebab-case (`use-` prefix) |
| Hook functions | `useUsers` | camelCase (`use` prefix) |
| Data files | `stack.data.ts` | kebab-case |
| Store files | `counter.store.ts` | kebab-case |
| Icons | `ReactIcon` | PascalCase (`Icon` suffix) |
| Types & interfaces | `User`, `SiteConfig` | PascalCase (no `Type` suffix) |
| Type files | `site-config.types.ts` | kebab-case |
| Constants | `nav.constants.ts` | kebab-case |
| Schema files | `newsletter.schema.ts` | kebab-case |

- **Short aliases:** Prefer `@/ui`, `@/hooks`, `@/data`, `@/schemas`, `@/layout` over the long form (`@/components/ui`). Both resolve identically via `tsconfig.json` paths, but short aliases are the house style.
- **Barrel exports:** Every folder that is imported from elsewhere MUST expose an `index.ts` re-exporting its public API.
- **Named exports only:** No default exports for components, hooks, stores, or utilities (Next.js `page.tsx`/`layout.tsx`/etc. are the only exception, since the framework requires default exports there).

## Bans

- Long-form imports when a short alias exists (`@/components/ui/button` when `@/ui` is available).
- Relative parent imports (`../../lib/utils`).
- `IUser`/`TUser` style prefixes.
- Default exports outside of Next.js special files.

## Correct Implementation

<example>
```ts
import { useUsers } from "@/hooks";
import { Button, Input } from "@/ui";
import { NAV_LINKS } from "@/constants";
```
</example>

## Incorrect Implementation

<incorrect-example>
```ts
import { useUsers } from "../../../hooks/use-users";
import Button from "@/components/ui/button";
```
</incorrect-example>
